Quote:  PUBLIC NOTICE is hereby given that the Opio River Board intends on Wednesday, 7th March, 1923, to make, pursuant to Section 87 of "The River Boards Act, 1908," and of amendments thereof, and Sections 48 and 50 of "The Rating Act, 1908," and its amendments - A GENERAL RATE OF 7/8d in the GBP in Grade One .. on the Rateable Value of all lands within the Opio River District for the year commencing on 1st April, 1922, and ending on 31st March, 1923, and payable in one sum of 14th March, 1923.
