Quote:  A resolution was passed unanimously - "That the Government be asked to pass an Act forming a central River Board, comprising and amalgamating the existing River Boards Districts, the districts to be divided into wards of as nearly as possible equal rating value, each ward returning one member or more, the rating basis to be the same as now existing, with power to obtain loans."
